    {
        "content": "<p>Oh, great, I didn't know.</p>\n<p>That suggests that maybe we should try to simplify life and not require people to know what backend they're actually getting, e.g. #search just does something.</p>",
        "id": 506644647,
        "sender_full_name": "Kim Morrison",
        "timestamp": 1742365946
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Agreed. We can keep the present commands, and also have an option to set the backend for <code>#search</code>. In tactic mode we can have the proof-state based backend if <code>#search</code> is given without a parameter.</p>\n<p>My only mild concern is triggering <code>#search</code> without arguments while the user has not yet typed the argument. Given the automatic delay before elaboration, this may not be such an issue.</p>\n<p>I can go ahead and implement this if the design seem fine.</p>",
